obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (15747)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15747&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Enemy`
  line `Property Act, 1968.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1*** and it applies also to all citizens of India outside India`
  line `and to branches and agencies outside India of companies or bodies corporate registered or`
  line `incorporated in India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 10th day of July, 1968.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (15748)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15748&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) "Custodian" means the Custodian of Enemy Property for India appointed or deemed to`
  line `have been appointed under section 3 and includes a Deputy Custodian and an Assistant Custodian`
  line `of Enemy Property appointed or deemed to have been appointed under that section;`
  line
  line `(b) "enemy" or "enemy subject" or "enemy firm" means a person or country who or which`
  line `was an enemy, ^1[an enemy subject including his legal heir and successor whether or not a citizen`
  line `of India or the citizen of a country which is not an enemy or the enemy, enemy subject or his legal`
  line `heir and successor who has changed his nationality] or`
  line `^2[an enemy firm, including its succeeding`
  line `firm whether or not partners or members of such succeeding firm are citizen of India or the citizen`
  line `of a country which is not an enemy or such firm which has changed its nationality], as the case`
  line `may be, under the Defence of India Act, 1962 (51 of 1962), and the Defence of India Rules, 1962`
  line `^3[or the Defence of India Act, 1971 (42 of 1971) and the Defence of India Rules, 1971], but`
  line `^4[does not include a citizen of India other than those citizens of India, being the legal heir and`
  line `successor of the "enemy" or "enemy subject" or "enemy firm--].`
  line
  line `^5[Explanation 1.--For the purposes of this clause, the expression "does not include a citizen`
  line `of India" shall exclude and shall always be deemed to have been excluded those citizens of India,`
  line `who are or have been the legal heir and successor of an "enemy" or an "enemy subject" or an`
  line `"enemy firm" which or who has ceased to be an enemy due to death, extinction, winding up of`
  line `business or change of nationality or that the legal heir and successor is a citizen of India or the`
  line `citizen of a country which is not an enemy.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the purposes of this clause, it is hereby clarified that nothing contained`
  line `in this Act shall affect any right of the legal heir and successor referred to in this clause (not being`
  line `inconsistent to the provisions of this Act) which have been conferred upon him under any other`
  line `law for the time being in force;]`
  line
  line `(c) "enemy property" means any property for the time being belonging to or held or managed`
  line `on behalf of an enemy, an enemy subject or an enemy firm:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an individual enemy subject dies in the territories to which this Act`
  line `extends, ^5[or dies in any territory outside India], any property which immediately before his death, belonged to or was held by him or was`
  line `managed on his behalf, may, notwithstanding his death, continue to be regarded as enemy`
  line `property for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `^6[Explanation 1.--For the purposes of this clause, it is hereby clarified that "enemy property"`
  line `shall, notwithstanding that the enemy or the enemy subject or the enemy firm has ceased to be an`
  line `enemy due to death, extinction, winding up of business or change of nationality or that the legal`
  line `heir and successor is a citizen of India or the citizen of a country which is not an enemy, continue`
  line `and always be deemed to be continued as an enemy property.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the purposes of this clause, the expression "enemy property" shall mean`
  line `and include and shall be deemed to have always meant and included all rights, titles and interest`
  line `in, or any benefit arising out of, such property;]`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2017, s. 2 for enemy subject (w.e.f. 10-7-1968).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 10-7-1968).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 40 of 1977, s. 3 (w.e.f. 27-9-1977).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 3 of 2017, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 10-7-1968).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 2, for ibid. (w.e.f. 10-7-1968).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 3 of 2017, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10-7-1968).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (15749)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Appointment of custodian of Enemy property for India and Deputy custodian, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1977, s. 4 (w.e.f. 27-9-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15749&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint a Custodian of Enemy`
  line `Property for Indian and one or more Deputy Custodians and Assistant Custodians or Enemy Property`
  line `for such local areas as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Custodian of Enemy Property for Indian and any Deputy Custodian or Assistant`
  line `Custodian of Enemy Property appointed under the Defence of India Rules, 1962 ^1[or the Defence of`
  line `India Rules, 1971, as the case may be], shall be deemed to have been appointed under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (15750)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of Inspectors of Enemy property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid (w.e.f. 27-9-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15750&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, either`
  line `generally or for any particular area, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint one or more`
  line `Inspectors of Enemy Property for securing compliance with the provisions of this Act and may, by`
  line `general or special order, provide for the distribution and allocation of the work to be performed by`
  line `them for securing such compliance:`
  line
  line `Provided that every Inspector of Enemy Firms appointed under the Defence of India Rules, 1962`
  line ^1
  line `[or the Defence of India Rules, 1971, as the case may be], shall be deemed to be an Inspector of`
  line `Enemy Property appointed under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (15751)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Property vested in the Custodian of Enemy property for India under the Defence of India Rules, 1962, to continue to vest in Custodian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15751&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] Notwithstanding the expiration of the`
  line `Defence of India Act, 1962 (51 of 1962), and the Defence of India Rules, 1962, all enemy property`
  line `vested before such expiration in the Custodian of Enemy Property for India appointed under the said`
  line `Rules and continuing to vest in him immediately before the commencement of this Act, shall, as from`
  line `such commencement, vest in the Custodian.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) Notwithstanding the expiration of the Defence of India Act, 1971 (12 of 1971) and the`
  line `Defence of India Rules, 1971, all enemy property vested before such expiration in the Custodian of`
  line `Enemy Property for India appointed under the said Rules and continuing to vest in him immediately`
  line `before the commencement of the Enemy Property, (Amendment) Act, 1977 (40 of 1977) shall, as`
  line `from such commencement, vest in the custodian.]`
  line
  line `^3[(3) The enemy property vested in the Custodian shall, notwithstanding that the enemy or the`
  line `enemy subject or the enemy firm has ceased to be an enemy due to death, extinction, winding up of`
  line `business or change of nationality or that the legal heir and successor is a citizen of India or the citizen`
  line `of a country which is not an enemy, continue to remain, save as otherwise provided in this Act, vested`
  line `in the Custodian.`
  line
  line `Explanation—.For the purposes of this sub-section, "enemy property vested in the Custodian"`
  line `shall include and shall always be deemed to have been included all rights, titles, and interest in, or any`
  line `benefit arising out of, such property vested in him under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 5 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-9-1977).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 6, for ibid. (w.e.f. 27-9-1977).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 3 of 2017, s. 3 (w.e.f. 10-7-1968).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (48986)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Issue of certificate by Custodian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2017, s. 4 (w.e.f. 7-1-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=48986&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Issue of certificate by Custodian. —The Custodian may, after making such inquiry as he`
  line `deems necessary, by order, declare that the property of the enemy or the enemy subject or the enemy`
  line `firm described in the order, vests in him under this Act and issue a certificate to this effect and such`
  line `certificate shall be the evidence of the facts stated therein.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_b:
  sectionId (48987)
  sectionNo 5B
  orderNo 7
  title `Law of succession or any custom or usage not to apply to enemy property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-7-1968).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=48987&sectionno=5B&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[5B. Law of succession or any custom or usage not to apply to enemy property.—Nothing`
  line `contained in any law for the time being in force relating to succession or any custom or usage`
  line `governing succession of property shall apply in relation to the enemy property under this Act and no`
  line `person (including his legal heir and successor) shall have any right and shall be deemed not to have`
  line `any right (including all rights, titles and interests or any benefit arising out of such property) in`
  line `relation to such enemy property.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, the expressions "custom" and "usage" signify any`
  line `rule which, having been continuously and uniformly observed for a long time, has obtained the force`
  line `of law in the matters of succession of property.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (15752)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 8
  title `Transfer of property vested in Custodian by enemy on enemy subject or enemy firm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for section 6 (w.e.f. 10-7-1968).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15752&sectionno=6&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[6. Prohibition to transfer any property vested in Custodian by an enemy, enemy subject or`
  line `enemy firm.—(1) No enemy or enemy subject or enemy firm shall have any right and shall never be`
  line `deemed to have any right to transfer any property vested in the Custodian under this Act, whether`
  line `before or after the commencement of this Act and any transfer of such property shall be void and shall`
  line `always be deemed to have been void.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any property vested in the Custodian under this Act had been transferred, before the`
  line `commencement of the Enemy Property (Amendment and Validation) Act, 2017, by an enemy or`
  line `enemy subject or enemy firm and such transfer has been declared, by an order, made by the Central`
  line `Government, to be void, and the property had been vested or deemed to have been vested in the`
  line `Custodian [by virtue of the said order made under section 6, as it stood before its substitution by`
  line `section 6 of the Enemy Property (Amendment and Validation) Act, 2017] such property shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, decree or order of any court, tribunal or other`
  line `authority, continue to vest or be deemed to have been vested in the Custodian and no person`
  line `(including an enemy or enemy subject or enemy firm) shall have any right or deemed to have any`
  line `right (including all rights, titles and interests or any benefit arising out of such property) over the said`
  line `property vested or deemed to have been vested in the Custodian.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (15753)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 9
  title `Payment to Custodian of money otherwise payable to an enemy, enemy subject or enemy firm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-9-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15753&sectionno=7&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any sum payable by way of dividend, interest, share profits or otherwise to or for the`
  line `benefit of an enemy or an enemy subject or an enemy firm shall, unless otherwise ordered by the`
  line `Central Government, be paid by the person by whom such sum would have been payable but for the`
  line `prohibition under the Defence of India Rules, 1962 ^1[or the Defence of India Rules, 1971, as the case`
  line `may be], to the Custodian or such person as may be authorised by him in this behalf and shall be held`
  line `by the Custodian or such person subject to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In cases in which money would, but for the prohibition under the Defence of India`
  line `Rules, 1962`
  line `^1[or the Defence of India Rules, 1971, as the case may be], be payable in a foreign`
  line `currency to or for the benefit of an enemy or an enemy subject or an enemy firm (other than cases in`
  line `which money is payable under a contract in which provision is made for specified rate of exchange),`
  line `the payment shall be made to the Custodian in rupee currency at the middle official rate of exchange`
  line `fixed by the Reserve Bank of India on the date on which the payment became due to that enemy,`
  line `enemy subject or enemy firm.`
  line
  line `(3) The Custodian shall, subject to the provisions of section 8, deal with any money paid to him`
  line `under the Defence of India Rules, 1962 ^1[or the Defence of India Rules, 1971, as the case may be] or`
  line `under this Act and any property vested in him under this Act in such manner as the Central`
  line `Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (15754)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 10
  title `Powers of Custodian In respect of enemy property vested in him.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15754&sectionno=8&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) With respect to the`
  line `property vested in the Custodian under this Act, the Custodian may take or authorise the taking of`
  line `such measures as he considers necessary or expedient for preserving such property till it is disposed of`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this Act.]`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, the Custodian or such person as`
  line `may be specifically authorised by him in this behalf, may, for the said purpose,`
  line
  line `(i) carry on the business of the enemy;`
  line
  line `^2[(ia) fix and collect the rent, standard rent, lease rent, licence fee or usage charges, as the case`
  line `may be, in respect of enemy property;]`
  line
  line `(ii) take action for recovering any money due to the enemy;`
  line
  line `(iii) make any contract and execute any document in the name and on behalf of the enemy;`
  line
  line `(iv) institute, defend or continue any suit or other legal proceeding, refer any dispute to`
  line `arbitration and compromise any debts, claims or liabilities;`
  line
  line `^3[(iva) secure vacant possession of the enemy property by evicting the unauthorised or illegal`
  line `occupant or trespasser and remove unauthorised or illegal constructions, if any].`
  line
  line `(v) raise on the security of the property such loans as may be necessary;`
  line
  line `(vi) incur out of the property any expenditure including the payment of any taxes, duties,`
  line `cesses and rates to Government or to any local authority and of any wages, salaries, pensions,`
  line `provident fund contributions to, or in respect of, any employee of the enemy and the repayment of`
  line `any debts due by the enemy to persons other than enemies;`
  line
  line `(vii) transfer by way of sale, mortgage or lease or otherwise dispose of any of the properties;`
  line
  line `(viii) invest any moneys held by him on behalf of enemies for the purchase of Treasury Bills`
  line `or such other Government securities as may be approved by the Central Government for the`
  line purpose;
  line
  line `(ix) make payments to the enemy and his dependents;`
  line
  line `(x) make payments on behalf of the enemy to persons other than those who are enemies, of`
  line `dues outstanding on the 25th October, 1962 ^4[or on the 3rd December, 1971]; and`
  line
  line `(xi) make such other payments out of the funds of the enemy as may be directed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.In this sub-section and in sections 10 and 17, enemy includes an enemy`
  line `subject and an enemy firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2017, s. 7, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 10-7-1968).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-7-1968).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-7-1968).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 40 of 1977, s. 8 (w.e.f. 29-7-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (48980)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 11
  title `Sale of Property by Custodian`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2017, s. 8 (w.e.f. 7-1-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=48980&sectionno=8A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Sale of property by Custodian.—(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `judgment, decree or order of any court, tribunal or other authority or any law for the time being in`
  line `force, the Custodian may, within such time as may be specified by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf, dispose of whether by sale or otherwise, as the case may be, with prior approval of the`
  line `Central Government, by general or special order, enemy properties vested in him immediately`
  line `before the date of commencement of the Enemy Property (Amendment and Validation) Act, 2017`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this Act, as amended by the Enemy Property (Amendment`
  line `and Validation) Act, 2017.`
  line
  line `(2) The Custodian may, for the purpose of disposal of enemy property under sub-section (1),`
  line `make requisition of the services of any police officer to assist him and it shall be the duty of such`
  line `officer to comply with such requisition.`
  line
  line `(3) The Custodian shall, on disposal of enemy property under sub-section (1) immediately`
  line `deposit the sale proceeds into the Consolidated Fund of India and intimate details thereof to the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Custodian shall send a report to the Central Government at such intervals, as it may`
  line `specify, for the enemy properties disposed of under sub-section (1), containing such details,`
  line `(including the price for which such property has been sold and the particulars of the buyer to`
  line `whom the properties have been sold or disposed of and the details of the proceeds of sale or`
  line `disposal deposited into the Consolidated Fund of India) as it may specify.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may, by general or special order, issue such directions to the`
  line `Custodian on the matters relating to disposal of enemy property under sub-section (1) and such`
  line `directions shall be binding upon the Custodian and the buyer of the enemy properties referred to`
  line `in that sub-section and other persons connected to such sale or disposal.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may, by general or special order, make such guidelines for`
  line `disposal of enemy property under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the Central Government may direct`
  line `that disposal of enemy property under sub-section (1) shall be made by any other authority or`
  line `Ministry or Department instead of Custodian and in that case all the provisions of this section`
  line `shall apply to such authority or Ministry or Department in respect of disposal of enemy property`
  line `under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) to (7), the Central Government`
  line `may deal with or utilise the enemy property in such manner as it may deem fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (15755)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 12
  title `Exemption from attachment, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15755&sectionno=9&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `All enemy property vested in the Custodian under this`
  line `Act shall be exempt from attachment, seizure or sale in execution of decree of a civil court or orders`
  line `of any other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (15756)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 13
  title `Transfer of securities belonging to an enemy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15756&sectionno=10&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in exercise of the powers`
  line `conferred by section 8, the Custodian proposes to sell any security issued by a company and`
  line `belonging to an enemy, the company may, with the consent of the Custodian, purchase the securities,`
  line `notwithstanding anything to the contrary in any law or in any regulations of the company and any`
  line `securities so purchased may be re-issued by the company as and when it thinks fit so to do.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Custodian executes and transfers any securities issued by a company, the company`
  line `shall, on receipt of the transfer and an order in this behalf from the Custodian, register the securities in`
  line `the name of the transferee, notwithstanding that the regulations of the company do not permit such`
  line `registration in the absence of the certificate, script or other evidence of title relating to the securities`
  line `transferred:`
  line
  line `Provided that any such registration shall be without prejudice to any lien or charge in favour of`
  line `the company and to any other lien or charge of which the Custodian gives express notice to the`
  line company.
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, "securities" includes shares, stocks, bonds, debentures and`
  line `debenture stock but does not include bills of exchange.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (48981)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to issue certificate of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2017, s. 9 (w.e.f. 7-1-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=48981&sectionno=10A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[10A. Power to issue certificate of sale.—(1) Where the Custodian proposes to sell any enemy`
  line `immovable property vested in him, to any person, he may on receipt of the sale proceeds of such`
  line `property, issue a certificate of sale in favour of such person and such certificate of sale shall,`
  line `notwithstanding the fact that the original title deeds of the property have not been handed over to the`
  line `transferee, be valid and conclusive proof of ownership of such property by such person.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, the certificate of`
  line `sale, referred to in sub-section (1), issued by the Custodian shall be a valid instrument for the`
  line `registration of the property in favour of the transferee and the registration in respect of enemy`
  line `property for which such certificate of sale had been issued by the Custodian, shall not be refused on`
  line `the ground of lack of original title deeds in respect of such property or for any such other reason.].`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (15757)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power of Custodian to summon persons and call for documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2017, s. 10 (w.e.f. 7-1-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15757&sectionno=11&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Custodian may,`
  line `by notice in writing, require any person whom he believes to be capable of giving information`
  line `concerning any enemy property to attend before him at such time and place as may be specified in the`
  line `notice and examine any such person concerning the same, reduce his statement to writing and require`
  line `him to sign it.`
  line
  line `(2) The Custodian may, by notice in writing, require any person whom he believes to have in his`
  line `possession or control any account book, letter book, invoice, receipt or other document of whatever`
  line `nature relating to any enemy property, to produce the same or cause the same to be produced before`
  line `the Custodian at such time and place as may be specified in the notice and to submit the same to his`
  line `examination and to allow copies of any entry therein or any part thereof to be taken by him.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) The Custodian, Deputy Custodian or Assistant Custodian shall have, for the purposes of`
  line `exercising powers or discharging his functions under this Act, the same powers as are vested in a civil`
  line `court under the Code of Civil Procedure,1908 (5 of 1908), while dealing with any case under this Act,`
  line `in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) requiring the discovery and inspection of documents;`
  line
  line `(b) enforcing the attendance of any person, including any officer dealing with land, revenue`
  line `and registration matters, banking officer or officer of a company and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(c) compelling the production of books, documents and other records; and`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (15758)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 16
  title `Protection for complying with orders of Custodian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15758&sectionno=12&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Where any order with respect to any`
  line `money or property is addressed to any person by the Custodian and accompanied by a certificate of`
  line `the Custodian that the money or property is money property vested in him under this Act, the`
  line `certificate shall be evidence of the facts stated therein and if that person complies with the orders of`
  line `the Custodian, he shall not be liable to any suit or other legal proceeding by reason only of such`
  line compliance.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (15759)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 17
  title `Validity of action taken in pursuance of orders of Custodian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15759&sectionno=13&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Where under this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) any money is paid to the Custodian; or`
  line
  line `(b) any property is vested in the Custodian or an order is given to any person by the Custodian`
  line `in relation to any property which appears to the Custodian to be enemy property vested in him`
  line `under this Act,`
  line
  line `neither the payment, vesting nor order of the Custodian nor any proceedings in consequence thereof`
  line `shall be invalidated or affected by reason only that at a material time,—`
  line
  line `(i) some person who was or might have been interested in the money or property, and who`
  line `was an enemy or an enemy firm, had died or had ceased to be an enemy or an enemy firm; or`
  line
  line `(ii) some person who was so interested and who was believed by the Custodian to be an`
  line `enemy or an enemy firm, was not an enemy or an enemy firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (15760)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 18
  title `Proceedings against companies whose assets vest in Custodian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15760&sectionno=14&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Where the enemy`
  line `property vested in the Custodian under this Act consists of assets of a company, no proceeding, civil`
  line `or criminal, shall be instituted under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), against the company, or`
  line `any director, manager or other officer thereof except with the consent in writing of the Custodian.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (15761)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 19
  title `Returns as to enemy property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15761&sectionno=15&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Custodian may call for from persons who, in his`
  line `opinion, have any interest in, or control over, any enemy property vested in him under this Act, such`
  line `returns as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person from whom a return is called for under sub-section (1) shall be bound to submit`
  line `such return within the prescribed period.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (15762)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 20
  title `Registers of returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15762&sectionno=16&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) All returns relating to enemy property submitted to the Custodian`
  line `under this Act shall be recorded in such registers as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) All such registers shall be open to inspection subject to the payment of such fees as may be`
  line `prescribed and to such reasonable restrictions as the Custodian may impose, to any person who, in the`
  line `opinion of the Custodian, is interested in any particular enemy property as a creditor or otherwise and`
  line `any such person may also obtain a copy of the relevant portion from the registers on payment of the`
  line `prescribed fees.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (15763)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 21
  title `Levy of fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15763&sectionno=17&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `There shall be levied by the Custodian fees equal to`
  line `^1[five per centum]`
  line of—
  line
  line `(a) the amount of moneys paid to him;`
  line
  line `(b) the proceeds of the sale or transfer of any property which has been vested in him under`
  line `this Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) the value of the residual property, if any, at the time of its transfer to the original owner or`
  line `other person specified by the Central Government under section 18:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of an enemy whose property is allowed by the Custodian to be managed`
  line `by some person specially authorised in that behalf, there shall be levied a fee of`
  line `^2[five per centum] of`
  line `the gross income of the enemy or such less fee as may be specifically fixed by the Central`
  line `Government after taking into consideration the cost of direct management incurred by that`
  line `Government, the cost of superior supervision and any risks that may be incurred by that Government`
  line `in respect of the management:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, reduce`
  line `or remit the fees leviable under this sub-section in any special case or class of cases.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this sub-section “gross income of the enemy” means income derived out of the`
  line `properties of the enemy vested in the Custodian under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The value of any property for the purpose of assessing the fees shall be the price which, in the`
  line `opinion of the Central Government or of an authority empowered in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government, such property would fetch if sold in the open market.`
  line
  line `(3) The fees in respect of property may be levied out of any proceeds of the sale or transfer`
  line `thereof or out of any income accrued therefrom or out of any other property belonging to the same`
  line `enemy and vested in the Custodian under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The fees levied under this section shall be credited to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Act 3 of 2017, s. 11, for “two per centum” (w.e.f. 7-1-2016).`
  line
  line `2.Subs. by Act 3 of 2017, s. 11, for “two per centum” (w.e.f. 7-1-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (15764)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title `Transfer of property vested as enemy property in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s.12, ibid., for section 18 (w.e.f. 7-1-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15764&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `^1[18. Transfer of property vested as enemy property in certain cases.—The Central`
  line `Government may, on receipt of a representation from a person, aggrieved by an order vesting a`
  line `property as enemy property in the Custodian within a period of thirty days from the date of receipt of`
  line `such order or from the date of its publication in the Official Gazette, whichever is earlier and after`
  line `giving a reasonable opportunity of being heard, if it is of the opinion that any enemy property vested`
  line `in the Custodian under this Act and remaining with him was not an enemy property, it may by general`
  line `or special order, direct the Custodian that such property vested as enemy property in the Custodian`
  line `may be transferred to the person from whom such property was acquired and vested in the Custodian.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_a:
  sectionId (48982)
  sectionNo 18A
  orderNo 23
  title `Income not liable to be returned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-7-1968).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=48982&sectionno=18A&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [18A. Income not liable to be returned.—Any income received in respect of the enemy`
  line `property by the Custodian shall not, notwithstanding that such property had been transferred by way`
  line `of sale under section 8A or section 18, as the case may be, to any other person, be returned or liable to`
  line `be returned to such person or any other person.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_b:
  sectionId (48983)
  sectionNo 18B
  orderNo 24
  title `Exclusion of jurisdiction of civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2017, s.14 (w.e.f. 7-1-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=48983&sectionno=18B&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_18_b_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[18B. Exclusion of jurisdiction of civil courts.Save as otherwise provided in this Act, no`
  line `civil court or authority shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or proceedings in respect of any`
  line `property, subject matter of this Act, as amended by the Enemy Property (Amendment and Validation)`
  line `Act, 2017, or any action taken by the Central Government or the Custodian in this regard.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_c:
  sectionId (48984)
  sectionNo 18C
  orderNo 25
  title `Appeal to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_c_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 3 of 2017, s.14 (w.e.f. 7-1-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=48984&sectionno=18C&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_18_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[18C. Appeal to High Court.--Any person aggrieved by an order of the Central Government`
  line `under section 18 of this Act, may, within a period of sixty days from the date of communication or`
  line `receipt of the order, file an appeal to the High Court on any question of fact or law arising out of such`
  line `orders, and upon such appeal the High Court may, after hearing the parties, pass such orders thereon`
  line `as it thinks proper:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from filing an appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not`
  line `exceeding sixty days.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "High Court" means the High Court of a State or Union territory in`
  line `which the property referred to in section 18 is situated.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (15765)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 26
  title `Protection of action taken under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15765&sectionno=19&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or the Custodian or an Inspector of Enemy Property for`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (15766)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 27
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15766&sectionno=20&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person makes any payment in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 7, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `six months, or with fine, or with both and the payment or dealing shall be void.`
  line `(2) If any person contravenes the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 10, he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.`
  line `(3) If any person fails to comply with a requisition made by the Custodian under sub-section (1)`
  line `or sub-section (2) of section 11, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred`
  line rupees.
  line `(4) If any person fails to submit the return under sub-section (2) of section 15, or furnishes such`
  line `return containing any particular which is false and which he knows to be false or does not believe to`
  line `be true, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (15767)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 28
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15767&sectionno=21&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company,`
  line `shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised`
  line `all due deligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has`
  line `been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent`
  line `or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or`
  line `other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line `(a) “company” means anybody corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line `(b) “director”, in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (15768)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 29
  title `Effect of laws inconsistent with the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2017, s. 16 (w.e.f. 10-7-1968)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15768&sectionno=22&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, ^1[(including any law of succession or any custom or usage in relation to succession of`
  line `property)].`
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (48985)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 30
  title Validation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-7-2010)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=48985&sectionno=22A&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[22A. Validation.—Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, decree or order of any`
  line `court, tribunal or other authority,—`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of this Act, as amended by the Enemy Property (Amendment and`
  line `Validation) Act, 2017, shall have and shall always be deemed to have effect for all purposes as if`
  line `the provisions of this Act, as amended by the said Act, had been in force at all material times;`
  line
  line `(b) any enemy property divested from the Custodian to any person under the provisions of this`
  line `Act, as it stood immediately before the commencement of the Enemy Property (Amendment and`
  line `Validation) Act, 2017, shall stand transferred to and vest or continue to vest, free from all`
  line `encumbrances, in the Custodian in the same manner as it was vested in the Custodian before such`
  line `divesting of enemy property under the provisions of this Act, as if the provisions of this Act, as`
  line `amended by the aforesaid Act, were in force at all material times;`
  line
  line `(c) no suit or other proceedings shall, without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing`
  line `provisions, be maintained or continued in any court or tribunal or authority for the enforcement of`
  line `any decree or order or direction given by such court or tribunal or authority directing divestment of`
  line `enemy property from the Custodian vested in him under section 5 of this Act, as it stood before the`
  line `commencement of the Enemy Property (Amendment and Validation) Act, 2017, and such enemy`
  line `property shall continue to vest in the Custodian under section 5 of this Act, as amended by the`
  line `aforesaid Act, as the said section, as amended by the aforesaid Act was in force at all material`
  line times;
  line
  line `(d) any transfer of any enemy property, vested in the Custodian, by virtue of any order of`
  line `attachment, seizure or sale in execution of decree of a civil court or orders of any tribunal or other`
  line `authority in respect of enemy property vested in the Custodian which is contrary to the provisions`
  line `of this Act, as amended by the Enemy Property (Amendment and Validation) Act, 2017, shall be`
  line `deemed to be null and void and notwithstanding such transfer, continue to vest in the Custodian`
  line `under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (15769)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15769&sectionno=23&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may make rules for carrying out the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for`
  line
  line `(a) the returns that may be called for by the Custodian under sub-section (1) of section 15 and`
  line `the period within which such returns shall be submitted under sub-section (2) of that section;`
  line
  line `(b) the registers in which the returns relating to enemy property shall be recorded under`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line `(c) the fees for the inspection of registers and for obtaining copies of the relevant portions`
  line `from the registers under sub-section (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which has to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session ^2[or in two or more successive sessions and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (d) omitted by s.18, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-1-2016)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 40 of 1977, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f. 27-9- 1977)`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (15770)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 32
  title `Certain orders made under the Defence of India Rules, 1962, to continue in force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15770&sectionno=24&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Every order which was made under the Defence of India Rules,`
  line `1962, by the Central Government or by the Custodian of Enemy Property for India appointed under`
  line `those Rules, relating to enemy property and which was in force immediately before the expiration`
  line `thereof shall, in so far as such order is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to`
  line `continue in force and to have been made under this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Every order which was made under the Defence of India Rules, 1971 by the Central`
  line `Government or by the Custodian of Enemy Property for India appointed under those Rules relating to`
  line `enemy property and which was in force immediately before the expiration thereof shall, in so far as`
  line `such order is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to continue in force and to`
  line `have been made under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 24 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-9-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-9-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (15771)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 33
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967&sectionId=15771&sectionno=25&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00006_196834_1517807319967
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Enemy Property Ordinance, 1968 (7 of 1968), is hereby`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall`
  line `be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
